<FIRST>u i BC-Libya-PlaneCrash 4thLd-Writethru a0494 07-27 0354</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Libya-Plane Crash, 4th Ld-Writethru, a0494,0362</SECOND>
<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>South Korean DC-10 Crashes at Tripoli, More Than 80 Survivors</HEAD>
<UNK>Eds: LEADS with 9 grafs to ADD Korean report plane reported engine
trouble and crash-landed short of the runway. Picks up 7th pvs, `Korean
Air ...'</UNK>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A South Korean DC-10 with 182 people
aboard crashed Thursday as the jetliner was about to land at
Tripoli airport in Libya, the official Libyan news agency JANA
reported.
   There was no word on deaths.
   JANA, monitored in Nicosia, said there were more than 80
survivors including the plane's captain. It said the jet crashed on
a runway after hitting two houses and several cars.
   In Seoul, South Korea, the Korean Broadcasting System said the
plane had reported engine trouble and crash-landed about three
miles short of the runway.
   JANA said the jet was on a scheduled flight from Seoul to
Tripoli and that the crash occurred at 7:30 a.m. (1:30 a.m. EDT).
   KBS said passengers included 181 Koreans, 10 foreigners and 15
crew members. It said many of the Koreans were workers for Daewoo
Corp. and Donga Construction Co. which have projects in Libya.
   There was no immediate explanation for the discrepancy between
the KBS and JANA reports.
   A United Air Lines DC-10 crashed in Sioux City, Iowa, last week,
killing 111 people. It had lost its tail engine and had hydraulic
problems.
   In Seoul, Korean Air officials confirmed the plane was down, but
had no details and said a passenger list was unavailable.
   Korean Air is a privately owned national flag carrier and the
largest of two Korean airlines.
   Formerly known as Korean Air Lines, it is known for its Flight
007, which Soviet fighter planes shot down over Soviet air space on
Sept. 1, 1983, killing 269 people.
   On Nov. 29, 1987, 115 people died when a Korean Air flight from
Baghdad, Iraq, to Seoul was lost over the Andaman Sea near Burma.
   South Korea charged North Korea with placing a bomb on the plane
and a self-confessed North Korean agent was sentenced to death in
connection with the incident earlier this year.
</TEXT>
