<HEAD>U.S. Tourist Dies At Scenic Waterfalls</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American tourist fell to his death at
Victoria Falls on Zimbabwe's border with Zambia, U.S. officials
said Thursday.
   John Morris, a student at the University of Chicago, was
visiting the 330-foot waterfall July 21 when he slipped on rocks
overlooking a gorge known as the Eastern Cataract, according to
Elizabeth Karonga of the U.S. Information Service in Harare.
   His body was recovered downstream, she said. Morris' age and
hometown were not immediately known.
   Viewing areas on both sides of the waterfalls are protected only
by thorn hedges and some wooden barriers. No deaths have been
reported there for several years.
   The Zambezi River cascades over a series of gorges about 1,708
yards in width to comprise Victoria Falls.
