<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Thailand-Crash     07-27 0119</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Thailand-Crash,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>11 Killed in Rail Crash in Thailand</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A crowded passenger train slammed into
another at a station in southern Thailand early Thursday, killing
at least 11 people and injuring 60 others, the state railway said.
   The accident occurred at the Huay Sai Nuae station in the
province of Petchburi, about 65 miles south of Bangkok, according
to Pranee Prasertanpron of the State Railway of Thailand.
   It was the fourth major train crash in Thailand since May.
   On May 24, eight people were killed and 57 injured when an
express train derailed in northern Thailand. In June, another 18
people were hurt when two trains collided head-on in central part
of the country.
</TEXT>
