<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Burma-Fire     07-27 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Burma-Fire,0142</SECOND>
<UNK>Mandalay Fire Kills 1 Razes 1,500 houses</UNK>
<DATELINE>RANGOON, Burma (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through the northern city of
Mandalay early Thursday, destroying more than 1,500 houses, leaving
9,500 people homeless and killing one person, sources said Thursday.
   An unspecified number of people suffered minor injuries in the
blaze, which began Wednesday night, according to the sources, who
asked not to be identified.
   There was no indication of the cause of the blaze.
   This was the third major fire in eight years in Mandalay. The
city, about 350 miles north of Rangoon, is Burma's second-largest
with a population of around 600,000.
   In 1981, 10 people were killed in a fire that destroyed 10,000
buildings and more than 35,000 were left homeless. In 1984, 23,000
people lost their homes in a fire that destroyed up to 2,700
buildings.
</TEXT>
