<FIRST>r a AM-MysteryVisitor     07-27 0358</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mystery Visitor,0370</SECOND>
<HEAD>Intruder Made Himself at Home When She Wasn't</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman wants to know who lounged on her couch,
messed up the bathroom, washed the linens, did the dishes and rang
up $1,600 worth of credit card charges while she was out of town.
   The woman, who asked not to be identified, spent two weeks out
of town on business and got her first hint that something was wrong
before she even returned home. She got a message that her credit
card was being used excessively, even though she had left it in her
dresser.
   A few days later, the credit card company said $1,600 in new
charges, mostly to a telephone sex-talk company in California, had
put her card over its limit, she said.
   Concerned that someone had broken into her apartment, she asked
a neighbor to check the doors and windows. Everything looked OK, he
told her.
   When she got home Tuesday, the door was locked and ``at first,
everything looked all right,'' she said. ``But then I started
noticing different things that weren't the way I left them.''
   The door leading to a balcony was open and the air conditioner
was off. The washer, dryer and dishwasher had been used.
   She found black hair in the dryer's lint trap; she has blonde
hair. The pillows on the couch were flattened; she had fluffed them
before leaving.
   Her bed wasn't made the way she makes it. And the mattress pad
had been damaged by someone who had put it through the dryer.
   Police said the unknown visitor must have had a key. The woman
said she hasn't given spare keys to anyone.
   In spite of the charges, she said all her credit cards were
still in her dresser drawer.
   She tried to keep her sense of humor.
   ``At least they left the liquor alone,'' she said. ``And they
must have ordered out, because I didn't leave a thing in the
fridge.''
   And she reached one other conclusion:
   ``It must have been a man, because the bathroom was a disaster.
I don't think any woman would have left it that disgusting.''
</TEXT>
