<HEAD>Library Gets Playboy on Microfilm, but Photos Still There</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A library's attempt to take the
centerfold out of Playboy magazine by switching to the microfilm
version has run into a problem _ the photos are still there.
   Under pressure by an anti-pornography group, the Grand Rapids
Board of Library Commissioners voted Tuesday to stop buying print
issues of Playboy and subscribe to the microfilmed version. At the
time, members believed the photos were edited out of the microfilm
version.
   But board President Jeanette Hayes said Wednesday the adult
magazine's entire contents are there for the microfilm viewer.
   The Michigan Decency Action Council had fought to make the
magazine inaccessible to minors.
   ``Even with the photos, (the microfilm version) still is
offering parents some more protection,'' council President Dar
VanderArk said Thursday. ``But I will be contacting board members
to see what can be done.''
