<FILEID>AP-NR-07-27-89 1345EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i BC-Palme-Chronology     07-27 0383</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Palme-Chronology,0397</SECOND>
<HEAD>Chronology of Palme Investigation</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Palme, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Key events in the Olof Palme case:
   Feb. 28, 1986 _ Prime Minister Olof Palme is shot from close
range on a Stockholm street corner at 11:21 p.m. after attending a
movie downtown.
   March 19 _ A 33-year-old suspect linked to an extreme right-wing
political party is freed after two weeks of interrogation when
police fail to cast doubt on his alibi.
   March-April _ Hundreds of Swedes with criminal records, among
them Christer Pettersson, are questioned and released.
   Jan. 20, 1987 _ Police round up 12 Kurdish exiles and arrest
three as murder suspects, capping a six-month investigation of the
militant Kurdish Workers Party. Stockholm Police Commissioner Hans
Holmer asserts an international conspiracy, but all the Kurds are
released for lack of evidence within 24 hours.
   Feb. 4 _ Holmer, who persists in following the Kurdish
connection despite objections of the state prosecutors, is fired as
head of the Palme task force and replaced by National Police
Commissioner Holger Romander.
   May 12 _ A judicial inquiry commission, which worked for 11
months to review the handling of the case, reprimands police for
bungling the 12 critical hours after the slaying. Its report paints
a picture of confusion and near- panic among the authorities.
   Nov. 12 _ The reward for information is raised 10 times the
earlier offer to about $8 million.
   June 7, 1988 _ Justice Minister Anna-Greta Leijon resigns under
fire six days after reports that she supported an amateur
investigation by publisher Ebbe Carlsson. Four months later, Police
Chief Nils-Erik Ahmansson also quit following criticism of his role
in the Ebbe Carlsson affair.
   Nov. 14 _ Hans Olvebro becomes the third leader of the
investigation and begins a review of information gathered since the
shooting.
   Dec. 14 _ Christer Pettersson is arrested.
   May 29, 1989 _ Pettersson is indicted for first-degree murder
and the attempted murder of Palme's wife, Lisbeth.
   June 5 _ Trial begins, Pettersson pleads innocent.
   June 19 _ Mrs. Palme identifies Pettersson in court as the man
she saw standing a few feet away just after her husband was shot.
Her testimony is the only evidence tying Pettersson to the scene of
the crime.
   Thursday _ Pettersson is convicted and sentenced to life
imprisonment.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
