<SECOND>AM-Nissan-UAW-Glance,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nissan at a Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Nissan-UAW, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SMYRNA, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here at a glance is the makeup of the
Nissan Motor Manufacturing Corp. U.S.A. plant:
   EMPLOYMENT: 2,400 hourly employees eligible to vote in the union
election; 800 management, engineering and other employees.
   PRODUCTION: Light trucks, Sentra car. Began making trucks in
June 1983, cars in March 1985. Produced 95,559 trucks and 119,120
cars in year ending March 31. Plans to begin making four-door sedan
in 1992, adding 2,000 jobs.
   PLANT: $760 million; 3.4 million square feet; 351 robots; annual
capacity of 240,000 vehicles.
   WAGES: $11.10 to $15.74 an hour plus $1.45-an-hour bonuses.
Other bonuses tied to quality and financial performance.
   ANNUAL PAYROLL: $104 million for entire work force.
   PARENT COMPANY: Nissan Motor Co. Ltd. of Tokyo.
