<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--LetterBomb     07-27 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Letter Bomb,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Explosion In Postal Sorting Center Kills One, Injures Two</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MARSEILLE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A letter bomb exploded Thursday in a
mail sorting center, killing one postal employee and injuring two
others, police said.
   Investigators said the small package was addressed to a foreign
destination, but did not say what country. They also did not say
where the package originated.
   There were no claims of responsibility for the bomb, which
police said apparently was not intended to go off before it was
delivered.
   The dead postal employee was identified as Noel Guerini, 52. Two
colleagues, Barthelemy Frau and Bruno Rivieri, were hospitalized
with serious injuries, police said.
   The explosion occurred on the sixth floor of a postal building
near the central train station in the Mediterranean port city of
Marseille.
</TEXT>
