<FIRST>r a AM-MotherKilled     07-27 0374</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mother Killed,0384</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mother Stabs Daughter, is Killed by Police</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By VIRGINIA BYRNE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who told her three children, ``The devil
is in you. I have to kill you,'' ignored warnings to drop her
knife, stabbed her 9-year-old daughter and was shot dead Thursday
by police, authorities said.
   The girl was in critical condition and undergoing surgery at
Brookdale Hospital. She had a deep wound in her abdomen and slashes
in her arm and finger, said Detective Joseph McConville.
   Her brothers, ages 6 and 7, were not physically harmed and were
brought to the police stationhouse to wait for their father, who
police said was working on Long Island.
   Police said the parents were separated and the father had
custody of the children. Neighbors said the children were on a
two-week visit with the mother that was part of the custody
agreement.
   The names of the family members were not made public.
   Police were called to the middle-class Brooklyn neighborhood
Thursday morning by neighbors who said a mother was threatening to
kill her children at a condominium.
   When four officers arrived, they could hear the children
screaming, McConville said.
   As one officer stood by the door to the apartment, the others
went into the backyard, where they found an open ground floor
window and could see the 35-year-old woman with a 14-inch knife,
and the three children cowering on a couch.
   One officer tried to persuade the woman to put down the knife,
but she refused, telling him, ``Children are evil,'' McConville
said. The police said she also told the children, ``The devil is in
you. I have to kill you.''
   The woman came to the window, slashed at the blinds with the
knife, then returned to her children and began stabbing her
9-year-old daughter repeatedly, the police spokesman said.
   Officer Andrew Boyle fired two shots at the woman, but she
continued to stab her daughter. Boyle jumped through the open
window to grab the woman, and when she tried to stab him, he fired
two more rounds and the woman fell to the floor, the spokesman said.
   She had been shot at least once in the chest and was pronounced
dead at the scene.
</TEXT>
