<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were higher at midday Thursday, as
the market continued to get a boost from Wall Street's Wednesday
gain and from the possibility of more speculative activity.
   ``The market feels good and firm,'' said one equities trader.
``There's a belief that we've bottomed out earlier in the week and
the next move is up.''
