<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
149,826 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
154,646, according to Ward's Automotive Reports.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
when 144,965 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said Thursday.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 86,851 cars this week, up
from 83,044 a week ago and from 73,541 in the same week in 1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 62,975,
compared with last week's 71,602 and last year's 71,424, Ward's
said.
   Canadian automakers were to build 19,098 cars this week, up from
12,101 a week ago and from last year's 9,577, Ward's said.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 16,894, up from
5,751 a week ago and from 8,941 in the same week last year.
