<HEAD>Republic Drops Prime Lending Rate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republic Bank, a small Philadelphia bank, on
Wednesday dropped its prime lending rate from 11 percent to 10{
percent, becoming the third bank in the nation to do so in recent
weeks.
   The prime is the rate that banks charge their most creditworthy
customers. It affects many other rates, such as those charged on
some credit cards and variable-rate mortgages.
   Southwest Bank of St. Louis dropped its prime to 10{ percent on
July 7 and Chase Manhattan Bank, based in New York, followed suit
several days later.
